node.text:
Here is a powerful word from one of our CEO’s @justinp ! Entrepreneurs, we have got to stop putting unrealistic expectations on our employees! Hold them accountable, yes, but at the end of the day, if you aren’t giving them any equity in the company, they are never going to truly care about the business as much as you do, so stop expecting it!

Of course, you can circumvent this by having an outstanding company culture centered around integrity, honesty and going the extra mile, but we have got to switch our mindset when it comes to what we believe we “deserve” from our employees.

Instead of thinking that anyone can do what you do for your business at 100% like you would, I instead choose to delegate tasks to the person who can get as close to 100% as possible. And in fact, I’ve found that if someone can even complete the task at 75-85% of my own personal standard, that is good enough for me to allow them to handle it and also gives them room to grow. This then lets me take on other more high level tasks in the business and better utilizes my time while avoiding MWA’s (Minimum Wage Activities).

So, my strategy is as follows:

Penetrate - Enter and learn a new task for the business.

Delegate - After becoming a practitioner at said task, give it away to a willing and able team member.

Automate - Utilize software and systems to automate/streamline this task.

Elevate - Use my newfound time to operate the business from a higher level.

And a quick newsflash for my business owners out there, IF YOUR EMPLOYEE DOES SOMETHING WRONG, IT’S YOUR FAULT NOT THEIRS!

If Sue the accountant does your books incorrectly, that’s your fault for not vetting her properly and no one else’s.

So, when you’re thinking about hiring help for a core function of your business, at the bare minimum, learn the jargon/basic functions of that area so you can speak intelligently with the potential hire and know if they are screwing you over or not.

And remember, hiring is guessing but firing is knowing.

Share this with someone you think can benefit from this and thanks for reading! ✈️
